{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire|type2=Fighting}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Pignite}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=498|prev=Tepig|nextnum=500|next=Emboar|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Pignite}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Pignite\n|jname=チャオブー\n|jtranslit=Chaobū\n|tmname=Chaoboo\n|category=Fire Pig\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|type2=Fighting\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Blaze\n|abilityd=Thick Fat\n|ndex=499\n|udex=005\n|u2dex=005\n|height-ftin=3\'03"\n|height-m=1.0\n|weight-lbs=122.4\n|weight-kg=55.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|expyield=146\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=31\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=45\n|evtotal=2\n|evat=2\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=pignite\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Pignite\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'チャオブー\'\'\' \'\'Chaoboo\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Fire|Fighting}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s from {{p|Tepig}} starting at [[level]] 17 and evolves into {{p|Emboar}} starting at level 36.\n\n==Biology==\nPignite is a bipedal, pig-like Pokémon. Its chubby body is orange with brown bands around its shoulders, sides, belly, hands, and from the back of its head down its snout. Yellow bands encircle its wrists, and swirled yellow designs bulge from its chest. It has a red pig-like nose, pointed ears, and two pointed teeth that protrude from its lower jaw. Its hands have two claws each, while its feet have only a single nail. Its tail is curled with a tuft of fur at the tip.\n\nPignite has a fire in its stomach, which it fuels with food. The intensity of this flame increases as fuel is added or when Pignite is angered. As the flame grows stronger, Pignite\'s speed increases. When in trouble, Pignite emits smoke. Its [[signature move]] is {{m|Heat Crash}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Ash Pignite.png|250px|thumb|left|Pignite in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Bianca\'s Pignite]]====\nPignite debuted in \'\'[[BW013|Minccino-Neat and Tidy!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{an|Bianca}}. He later evolved into Emboar before \'\'[[BW071|Search for the Clubultimate!]]\'\'.\n\n====[[Ash\'s Pignite]]====\n{{Ash}}\'s Tepig evolved into a Pignite in \'\'[[BW077|Evolution by Fire!]]\'\' while battling his former {{pkmn|Trainer}}, [[Shamus]].\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Pignite appeared in \'\'[[BW022|A Venipede Stampede!]]\'\', where it was used in an attempt to stop a swarm of {{p|Venipede}}.\n\nA Pignite appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[BW070|The Clubsplosion Begins!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Pignite appeared in \'\'[[SM034|A Crowning Moment of Truth!]]\'\', with one of them appearing in a flashback. They were among the Pokémon attending the [[Wela Fire Festival\u200e]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW013|Pignite|Ash\'s Pokédex|Pignite, the Fire Pig Pokémon and the evolved form of Tepig. Pignite\'s food converts into fuel for the flame that burns in its stomach, and when fuel burns in its stomach, its speed increases.}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW077|Pignite|Ash\'s Pokédex|Pignite, the Fire Pig Pokémon. Pignite moves faster when its internal flame becomes more intense. This also occurs when it gets angry.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Nite.png|thumb|170px|Pignite in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pocket Monsters BW: The Heroes of Fire and Thunder manga===\n{{main|Shin\'s Pignite}}\n{{OBP|Shin|FAT}} owned a Pignite in [[Pocket Monsters BW: The Heroes of Fire and Thunder]]. It evolved into an Emboar in \'\'[[FAT2|The King\'s Identity...!!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Bo}}\n{{adv|Black}}\'s {{p|Tepig}}, [[nickname]]d Tep, that he received from [[Professor Juniper]] evolved in \'\'[[PS479|The Case of the Missing Pokémon]]\'\', while battling [[Burgh]]\'s {{p|Dwebble}}. The day after finding and returning the missing Pokémon, Black renamed Tep to Nite. He has since evolved into an Emboar, and renamed Bo.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Pignite (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Fire|type2=Fighting}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=005}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=Fire|type2=Fighting}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=V}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|area=[[Evolution|Evolve]] {{p|Tepig}}}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|area=[[Evolution|Evolve]] {{p|Tepig}}}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry2/None|v=X|v2=Y}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Omega Ruby|v2=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|t2=FFF|area=[[Evolution|Evolve]] 